ğŸ§  C. Conceptual Restatement
	â€¢	Corporate default = â€œassets fall below debtâ€ (solvency failure).
	â€¢	Hedge-fund default = â€œcash buffer falls below margin callsâ€ (liquidity failure).
	â€¢	In both cases, we observe how often a volatile process (asset value or margin loss) crosses a barrier.
	â€¢	Because this frequency can be calculated from volatility and distance, we get a quantified default probability that naturally links to ratings and haircuts.

